Project Description
The project is implemented by three partners; Help Foundation, Doaba Foundation and participatory Development Initiatives (PDI). The project aims at;
1. Improving smallholders' household food security through promoting crop diversification andminor crops value chain in mono-cropping areas of district Rajanpur
2. Sustainable Livelihood through Medicinal Plants Business Promotion
3. Vegetables <(>&<)> Fruits Value Chain Capacity Building Project
In sindh the project aims at;
# 300 women farmers are mobilized by forming and strengthening 30 Women Farmers Organizations [WFOs] and 3 Women#s Producer Organizations [WPOs] in Mirpur SakroTehsil of District Thatta and women farmer cooperative societies [ POs] of Sindh are networked through the Federation of women#s agriculture cooperative societies
# Capacities and Skills of 100 WFO/WPO member women farmers are build in improved tomato production value chain in Mirpur Sakro Tehsil of District Thatta
# Skills and capacities of women 100 farmers are build in collective marketingof tomato to ensure fair prices for their tomato crops in Mirpur Sakro Tehsil of District Thatta
In Layyah district of Punjab province, the project is in the second year of its implementation and aims at establishing value chain of Herbal Plants. During the 1st year of the project partner Doaba undertook study on value chain of herbal plant, established demo plots, processed herbal plants to local market and supplied herbal medicine in local market.  During this (2nd) phase of the program Doaba will be more extensively focusing on market linkage to promote use of herbal products. To get that a market study will be undertaken to understand the market dynamics relevant to herbal plants. Which will serve as base to develop linkage with different market forces, besides the production and processing part will remain continued to maintain the supply chain.
In Rajanpur District of Punjab; partner Help Foundations aims that;
1. 720 small farming households (90% registeredcitizens) of District Rajanpur will be actively engaged in a duel-tier collective saving <(>&<)> lending mechanism established to fill the gap of their financial capacity for agricultural activities especiallyMungbean cultivation;
2. Mungbean yields will increase and small farmers# bargaining power will be strengthened through introduction of improved and modern farming methods, cash grants, seed bank establishment, value chain trainings and improved access to departmental facilitations;
3. 03 Farmer Associations will be established with their Mungbean collection/purchase, processing and collective marketing system through strengthening local capacities; and
4. Stakeholders# understanding of Mungbean Value Chain dynamics and issues will be enhanced throughcarrying out research initiatives on relevant subjects to provide the research-based stand for future advocacy/practice level programs on the subject.
